<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-03-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="713" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Select Committee on Purchase of <gloss type="from">Danish Islands</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">House of Representatives</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-03-31">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: I have the honor to submit herewith
                            an alleged report to the Danish Government from Captain W. Christmas
                            Dirckinck Holmfeld, relative to the purchase of the Danish West India
                                Islands.<note n="11" xml:id="d713fn23">
                                <hi rend="italic">See</hi> House Report No. 2749, 57th Congress, 1st
                                sess.</note> You will observe that in this so-called report certain
                            statements are made as to relations existing between yourself and the
                            author of the report. I have no doubt that at some time in the near
                            future the committee appointed by the House to investigate the matter of
                            this report will be glad to have you appear before them to make such
                            statement as to you may seem fitting.</p>
                        <p>Very respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">John Dalzell</hi>, <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Chairman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>